WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.479 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.479 --> 00:00:48.750 align:middle line:90%


00:00:48.750 --> 00:00:51.560 align:middle line:84%
>>900 years ago, the
holy city of Jerusalem

00:00:51.560 --> 00:00:56.110 align:middle line:84%
was conquered by Christianity's
First Crusade against Islam.

00:00:56.110 --> 00:01:00.430 align:middle line:84%
The victorious crusader knights
occupied the Muslim holy sites,

00:01:00.430 --> 00:01:04.650 align:middle line:84%
including the sacred Dome of
the Rock and the nearby Al Aqsa

00:01:04.650 --> 00:01:06.400 align:middle line:90%
Mosque.

00:01:06.400 --> 00:01:08.900 align:middle line:84%
The Crusaders
believed the Al Aqsa

00:01:08.900 --> 00:01:12.510 align:middle line:84%
rested on the ancient remains
of King Solomon's temple.

00:01:12.510 --> 00:01:15.570 align:middle line:84%
And the knights who
came to live there

00:01:15.570 --> 00:01:19.274 align:middle line:84%
were known ever after
as the Knights Templar.

00:01:19.274 --> 00:01:22.732 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:22.732 --> 00:01:43.962 align:middle line:90%


00:01:43.962 --> 00:01:45.670 align:middle line:84%
At the height of their
power, the Knights

00:01:45.670 --> 00:01:49.210 align:middle line:84%
of the Temple of Solomon were
the elite military spearhead

00:01:49.210 --> 00:01:52.360 align:middle line:90%
of the medieval Catholic Church.

00:01:52.360 --> 00:01:56.120 align:middle line:84%
The knights were unique, both
warrior and monk, utterly

00:01:56.120 --> 00:01:59.360 align:middle line:84%
dedicated to killing
and dying for their God.

00:01:59.360 --> 00:02:02.530 align:middle line:84%
The Templars were the epitome
of Christianity's crusade

00:02:02.530 --> 00:02:03.270 align:middle line:90%
against Islam.

00:02:03.270 --> 00:02:07.040 align:middle line:90%


00:02:07.040 --> 00:02:10.650 align:middle line:84%
The Knights Templar were not
just front-line soldiers;

00:02:10.650 --> 00:02:13.910 align:middle line:84%
they also constructed a
remarkable supply and support

00:02:13.910 --> 00:02:17.700 align:middle line:84%
network that enveloped
every nation in Europe.

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:21.020 align:middle line:84%
The Templar network acquired
vast business interests

00:02:21.020 --> 00:02:24.140 align:middle line:84%
in farming, shipping, and
banking, which eventually

00:02:24.140 --> 00:02:27.540 align:middle line:84%
turned the order into the most
powerful financial institution

00:02:27.540 --> 00:02:28.850 align:middle line:90%
in Europe.

00:02:28.850 --> 00:02:32.180 align:middle line:84%
In fact, the Order of
the Temple of Solomon

00:02:32.180 --> 00:02:35.055 align:middle line:84%
was the world's first
multinational corporation.

00:02:35.055 --> 00:02:40.030 align:middle line:90%


00:02:40.030 --> 00:02:42.770 align:middle line:84%
Just 200 years after
its foundation,

00:02:42.770 --> 00:02:45.050 align:middle line:84%
the Order's leaders
were burned alive

00:02:45.050 --> 00:02:46.470 align:middle line:90%
and its vast wealth seized.

00:02:46.470 --> 00:02:49.250 align:middle line:90%


00:02:49.250 --> 00:02:52.550 align:middle line:84%
Were the Templars
heretical devil worshippers

00:02:52.550 --> 00:02:56.040 align:middle line:84%
or innocent victims
of a greedy king?

00:02:56.040 --> 00:02:58.520 align:middle line:84%
Their sudden destruction was
so shocking to the people

00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:01.170 align:middle line:84%
of Europe that, for
centuries to come,

00:03:01.170 --> 00:03:05.170 align:middle line:84%
legends would grow up around the
remnants of the doomed order.

00:03:05.170 --> 00:03:09.890 align:middle line:84%
