00:15:54.490 --> 00:15:56.185 align:middle line:90%
and soon learned to fear battle.

00:15:56.185 --> 00:16:00.470 align:middle line:90%


00:16:00.470 --> 00:16:03.740 align:middle line:84%
As a result, the decision
to deploy a cavalry charge

00:16:03.740 --> 00:16:05.500 align:middle line:90%
was not taken lightly.

00:16:05.500 --> 00:16:07.680 align:middle line:84%
And Templar military
policy in the Holy Land

00:16:07.680 --> 00:16:09.540 align:middle line:90%
was, on the whole, cautious.

00:16:09.540 --> 00:16:12.900 align:middle line:90%


00:16:12.900 --> 00:16:16.000 align:middle line:84%
As the skill and reputation
of the Templars began to grow,

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:19.240 align:middle line:84%
so did their role in the overall
defense of the Crusader states.

00:16:19.240 --> 00:16:30.150 align:middle line:90%


00:16:30.150 --> 00:16:31.900 align:middle line:84%
In the second half
of the 12th century,

00:16:31.900 --> 00:16:35.480 align:middle line:84%
the Crusaders' 400-mile
coastal strip of the Holy Land

00:16:35.480 --> 00:16:38.740 align:middle line:84%
was based around the
cities of Antioch, Tripoli,

00:16:38.740 --> 00:16:40.020 align:middle line:90%
and the capital, Jerusalem.

00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:43.730 align:middle line:90%


00:16:43.730 --> 00:16:46.000 align:middle line:84%
The Christians controlled
the Mediterranean,

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:48.550 align:middle line:84%
which was vital for
supplies, especially

00:16:48.550 --> 00:16:52.220 align:middle line:84%
through the Port of
Acre, while mountains

00:16:52.220 --> 00:16:55.150 align:middle line:84%
on the eastern frontier
and the River Jordan

00:16:55.150 --> 00:16:57.206 align:middle line:84%
provided excellent
natural defenses.

00:16:57.206 --> 00:17:01.260 align:middle line:90%


00:17:01.260 --> 00:17:04.490 align:middle line:84%
Castles and fortifications,
many of them Templar,

00:17:04.490 --> 00:17:07.365 align:middle line:84%
guarded the main entry points
into the Christian states.

00:17:07.365 --> 00:17:16.569 align:middle line:90%


00:17:16.569 --> 00:17:18.859 align:middle line:10%
Although the Christian
sliver of the Holy Land

00:17:18.859 --> 00:17:22.190 align:middle line:10%
was surrounded by Islam,
political and religious

00:17:22.190 --> 00:17:24.690 align:middle line:10%
