00:28:04.570 --> 00:28:08.200 align:middle line:90%


00:28:08.200 --> 00:28:10.610 align:middle line:84%
The capture of Jerusalem
was the crowning moment

00:28:10.610 --> 00:28:13.900 align:middle line:84%
of a monumental career,
which had seen Saladin

00:28:13.900 --> 00:28:17.050 align:middle line:84%
unite the Islamic world
and drive out nearly all

00:28:17.050 --> 00:28:19.104 align:middle line:84%
the Crusaders from
the Holy Land.

00:28:19.104 --> 00:28:25.010 align:middle line:90%


00:28:25.010 --> 00:28:28.320 align:middle line:84%
The Templars had been almost
eliminated from the East.

00:28:28.320 --> 00:28:30.800 align:middle line:84%
But incredibly, they
had prepared themselves

00:28:30.800 --> 00:28:33.060 align:middle line:84%
for a disaster on
even this scale.

00:28:33.060 --> 00:28:35.880 align:middle line:90%


00:28:35.880 --> 00:28:38.600 align:middle line:84%
Since their foundation,
they had been constructing

00:28:38.600 --> 00:28:42.170 align:middle line:90%
an enormous support network.

00:28:42.170 --> 00:28:45.150 align:middle line:84%
This multinational
corporation had headquarters

00:28:45.150 --> 00:28:48.660 align:middle line:84%
in London and Paris and
was built with one aim,

00:28:48.660 --> 00:28:51.290 align:middle line:84%
to finance the Order's
front-line operations

00:28:51.290 --> 00:28:53.930 align:middle line:90%
in the East.

00:28:53.930 --> 00:28:55.700 align:middle line:84%
The Templars would
soon get their chance

00:28:55.700 --> 00:28:57.630 align:middle line:90%
to begin the fight back.

00:28:57.630 --> 00:28:59.980 align:middle line:84%
Saladin's victories
had sent shock waves

00:28:59.980 --> 00:29:02.190 align:middle line:84%
through Christian
Europe and ignited

00:29:02.190 --> 00:29:04.800 align:middle line:90%
a fever of religious enthusiasm.

00:29:04.800 --> 00:29:09.555 align:middle line:84%
The result would be the Third
Crusade, which in the year 1189

00:29:09.555 --> 00:29:12.690 align:middle line:84%
would set out to
recover the Holy Land.

